HEADWORD: Bow net
<hw>Bow" net`</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <sn>1.</sn> <def>A trap for lobsters,
being a wickerwork cylinder with a funnel-shaped entrance at one
end.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A net for catching birds.</def> <rj><au>J. H.
Walsh.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bow oar</ent>⟦br⟧
